dcterms:description: The Bi-DexHands dataset is a benchmark for bimanual dexterous manipulation, designed to facilitate the study of human-level dexterity in robotic systems. It includes a variety of tasks that mimic human motor skills and utilizes the Isaac Gym simulator for efficient reinforcement learning training.
dcterms:title: Bi-DexHands
